subsequent.name: Power up, beat it up II

characters.flavour: Bridget’s an overachiever and she’ll let you know it. Her giant mana-bot can take a hit and dish one out. She can stun her enemies and heal her friends. You can rely on Bridget to anchor the team.
characters.name: Bridget

characters.flavour: Eve leaves blood everywhere she goes. Her power is near unrivalled both up close and at range. She lives and dies by the sword — her frail defences makes any advance a risk. Then again, what’s a risk when Death’s a welcome friend?
characters.name: Eve

characters.flavour: Sar can crush the minds of the sternest warriors. He can strike behind walls and obstacles; he can also disable fighters by taking away their voice, their strength, or their sanity. When well protected, he is every soldier’s nightmare.
characters.name: Sar

characters.flavour: Don’t blink, or you might miss Zan. His natural mana abilities allow him to teleport himself and his allies around the battlefield. Slashing someone’s just like real estate — location, location, location.
characters.name: Zan

characters.flavour: People have different strengths — Kieran’s good at blowing people up. He can create explosions with mana, making him a handful at close quarters. Don’t think about running either, he can pull you back in with an energy wave.
characters.name: Kieran

characters.flavour: Daniel loves making things — obstacles, energy zones, vicious traps — he’s just a kid. He’d probably be recruited as a master builder If he didn’t join the revolution.
characters.name: Daniel

characters.flavour: An unthinking automaton, perfect for target practice.
characters.name: Robot

characters.flavour: Kids these days never take their jabs. Good thing you have old Galen here! You’ll be in tip-top shape in no time! Well… as long as it takes for him to tell you about his time at the Academy.
characters.name: Galen

characters.flavour: Nettis is crafty. She can load different crystals into her rifle and pick her poison. She can deal with traps and zones, she can heal, she can control space, she can even cover her allies. Bit of a know-it-all, really.
characters.name: Nettis
